OL,4,Cpay for therapy, say sub-postmasters
OL,6,F"It was horrendous, it was horrible...
OL,7,F25 years of my life has been ruined by
OL,8,Fthe Post Office," Parmod says.
OL,10,F"My children did actually ask me at
OL,11,Fthe time, 'Dad, have you taken the
OL,12,Fmoney?'. They were six and nine years
OL,13,Fold at the time."
OL,15,FMr Kalia says his health and
OL,16,Frelationships with his family have
OL,17,Fsuffered as a result of his wrongful
OL,18,Fconviction.
